      "callEndedTimestamp": null,
      "isPinned": false,
      "content": "I've tried googling this, but not having much luck yet. When opening the openroad-gui via librelane 'nom_tt_25C_5v00' timing corners are loaded and reported. I'm seeing a large gap between the slowest:'max_ss_125C_4v50' and fastest: 'min_ff_n40C_5v50' corners. Curious how I would load the other timing corners to visually see the paths, and maybe optimise macro placements. \n\nI've tried `read_spef --corner <file>`, but the corner names don't seem to be correct.",
      "author": {
        "id": "274535015969456128",
        "name": "greg.hashtag.9468",
        "discriminator": "0000",
        "nickname": "Greg",
        "color": null,
